            <title>[SOLR-531] rsyncd-start and snappuller should exit with different exit code when disabled</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-531</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the rsyncd-start and snappuller scripts get executed the scripts check if they are enabled or not. If they are disabled they exit with 1. The scripts exit with 1 on error as well. So you cannot decide in upstream scripts if really an error occurred or if they are only disabled.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
